User:Generate the lists of enumerations, classes and attributes from a given <Description>.
#Description 
The LabTracker software helps (i) doctors manage the requisition of tests and examinations for patients and (ii) patients book appointments for tests and examinations at a lab. For the remainder of this description, tests and examinations are used interchangeably. 

For a requisition, a doctor must provide their numeric practitioner number and signature for verification as well as their full name, their address, and their phone number. The signature is a digital signature, i.e., an image of the actual signature of the doctor. Furthermore, the doctor indicates the date from which the requisition is valid. The requisition must also show the patient?? information including their alpha-numeric health number, first name and last name, date of birth, address, and phone number. A doctor cannot prescribe a test for themselves but can prescribe tests to someone else who is a doctor. 

Several tests can be combined on one requisition but only if they belong to the same group of tests. For example, only blood tests can be combined on one requisition or only ultrasound examinations can be combined. It is not possible to have a blood test and an ultrasound examination on the same requisition. For each test, its duration is defined by the lab network, so that it is possible to schedule appointments accordingly. The duration of a test is the same at each lab. For some kinds of tests, it does not matter how many tests are performed. They take as long as a single test. For example, several blood tests can be performed on a blood sample, i.e., it takes as long to draw the blood sample for a single blood test as it does for several blood tests. 

A doctor may also indicate that the tests on a requisition are to be repeated for a specified number of times and interval. The interval is either weekly, monthly, every half year, or yearly. All tests on a requisition are following the same repetition pattern. 

The doctor and the patient can view the results of each test (either negative or positive) as well as the accompanying report. 

A patient is required to make an appointment for some tests while others are walk-in only. For example, x-ray examinations require an appointment, but blood tests are walk-in only (i.e., it is not possible to make an appointment for a blood test). On the other hand, some tests only require a sample to be dropped off (e.g., a urine or stool sample). 

To make an appointment for a requisition, a patient selects the desired lab based on the lab?? address and business hours. For requisitions with repeated tests, a patient is only allowed to make one appointment at a time. The confirmation for an appointment also shows a confirmation number, the date as well as start/end times, and the name of the lab as well as its registration number. It is possible to change or cancel an appointment at any time but doing so within 24 hours of the appointment incurs a change/cancellation fee. Each lab determines its own fee and business hours. All labs are open every day of the year and offer all tests. The business hours of a lab do not change from one week to the next. Each day a lab is open from the day?? start time to its end time, i.e., there are no breaks. 

AI:### Enumerations:
1. TestType
   - BLOOD
   - ULTRASOUND
   - XRAY
   - URINE
   - STOOL

2. RepetitionInterval
   - WEEKLY
   - MONTHLY
   - EVERY_HALF_YEAR
   - YEARLY

3. TestResult
   - POSITIVE
   - NEGATIVE

### Classes:
1. Doctor
   - Attributes:
     - practitionerNumber: int
     - signature: Image
     - fullName: String
     - address: String
     - phoneNumber: String

2. Patient
   - Attributes:
     - healthNumber: String
     - firstName: String
     - lastName: String
     - dateOfBirth: Date
     - address: String
     - phoneNumber: String

3. Requisition
   - Attributes:
     - doctor: Doctor
     - patient: Patient
     - tests: List<Test>
     - startDate: Date
     - repetitionTimes: int
     - repetitionInterval: RepetitionInterval

4. Test
   - Attributes:
     - testType: TestType
     - duration: int

5. Appointment
   - Attributes:
     - patient: Patient
     - lab: Lab
     - test: Test
     - confirmationNumber: String
     - date: Date
     - startTime: Time
     - endTime: Time
     - labRegistrationNumber: String

6. Lab
   - Attributes:
     - address: String
     - businessHours: List<BusinessHour>
     - testsOffered: List<Test>
     - changeCancellationFee: double

7. BusinessHour
   - Attributes:
     - day: DayOfWeek
     - startTime: Time
     - endTime: Time

### Note:
- Additional classes such as Image, Date, Time, DayOfWeek need to be defined based on the programming language being used.
- Associations and methods for the classes are not specified in this model but would be necessary for a complete implementation.

AI:Enumerations:
1. TestType(BLOOD, ULTRASOUND, XRAY, URINE, STOOL): Represents different types of tests that can be prescribed by doctors.
2. RepetitionInterval(WEEKLY, MONTHLY, EVERY_HALF_YEAR, YEARLY): Defines the intervals at which tests on a requisition can be repeated.
3. TestResult(POSITIVE, NEGATIVE): Indicates the result of each test as either positive or negative.

Classes:
1. Doctor(practitionerNumber: int, signature: Image, fullName: String, address: String, phoneNumber: String): Represents a doctor who can create test requisitions for patients.
2. Patient(healthNumber: String, firstName: String, lastName: String, dateOfBirth: Date, address: String, phoneNumber: String): Represents a patient who can book appointments for tests at a lab.
3. Requisition(doctor: Doctor, patient: Patient, tests: List<Test>, startDate: Date, repetitionTimes: int, repetitionInterval: RepetitionInterval): Represents a requisition created by a doctor for a patient with details of tests to be performed.
4. Test(testType: TestType, duration: int): Represents an individual test with its type and duration.
5. Appointment(patient: Patient, lab: Lab, test: Test, confirmationNumber: String, date: Date, startTime: Time, endTime: Time, labRegistrationNumber: String): Represents an appointment made by a patient for a specific test at a lab.
6. Lab(address: String, businessHours: List<BusinessHour>, testsOffered: List<Test>, changeCancellationFee: double): Represents a lab where tests can be conducted, with information about its address, business hours, tests offered, and fees.
7. BusinessHour(day: DayOfWeek, startTime: Time, endTime: Time): Represents the business hours of a lab on a specific day.

#Description 
The LabTracker software helps (i) doctors manage the requisition of tests and examinations for patients and (ii) patients book appointments for tests and examinations at a lab. For the remainder of this description, tests and examinations are used interchangeably. 

For a requisition, a doctor must provide their numeric practitioner number and signature for verification as well as their full name, their address, and their phone number. The signature is a digital signature, i.e., an image of the actual signature of the doctor. Furthermore, the doctor indicates the date from which the requisition is valid. The requisition must also show the patient?? information including their alpha-numeric health number, first name and last name, date of birth, address, and phone number. A doctor cannot prescribe a test for themselves but can prescribe tests to someone else who is a doctor. 

Several tests can be combined on one requisition but only if they belong to the same group of tests. For example, only blood tests can be combined on one requisition or only ultrasound examinations can be combined. It is not possible to have a blood test and an ultrasound examination on the same requisition. For each test, its duration is defined by the lab network, so that it is possible to schedule appointments accordingly. The duration of a test is the same at each lab. For some kinds of tests, it does not matter how many tests are performed. They take as long as a single test. For example, several blood tests can be performed on a blood sample, i.e., it takes as long to draw the blood sample for a single blood test as it does for several blood tests. 

A doctor may also indicate that the tests on a requisition are to be repeated for a specified number of times and interval. The interval is either weekly, monthly, every half year, or yearly. All tests on a requisition are following the same repetition pattern. 

The doctor and the patient can view the results of each test (either negative or positive) as well as the accompanying report. 

A patient is required to make an appointment for some tests while others are walk-in only. For example, x-ray examinations require an appointment, but blood tests are walk-in only (i.e., it is not possible to make an appointment for a blood test). On the other hand, some tests only require a sample to be dropped off (e.g., a urine or stool sample). 

To make an appointment for a requisition, a patient selects the desired lab based on the lab?? address and business hours. For requisitions with repeated tests, a patient is only allowed to make one appointment at a time. The confirmation for an appointment also shows a confirmation number, the date as well as start/end times, and the name of the lab as well as its registration number. It is possible to change or cancel an appointment at any time but doing so within 24 hours of the appointment incurs a change/cancellation fee. Each lab determines its own fee and business hours. All labs are open every day of the year and offer all tests. The business hours of a lab do not change from one week to the next. Each day a lab is open from the day?? start time to its end time, i.e., there are no breaks.

2. RepetitionInterval(WEEKLY, MONTHLY, HALF_YEARLY, YEARLY): Defines the intervals at which tests on a requisition can be repeated.
3. TestResult(NEGATIVE, POSITIVE): Indicates the result of a test as either negative or positive.

### Classes:
1. Doctor(practitionerNumber: numeric, signature: image, fullName: string, address: string, phoneNumber: string): Represents a doctor who can create test requisitions for patients.
2. Patient(healthNumber: alphanumeric, firstName: string, lastName: string, dateOfBirth: date, address: string, phoneNumber: string): Represents a patient for whom test requisitions are created by doctors.
3. Requisition(doctor: Doctor, patient: Patient, validFromDate: date, tests: List<Test>, repetitionInterval: RepetitionInterval, repetitionTimes: integer): Represents a requisition created by a doctor for a patient, including the tests to be performed and their repetition details.
4. Test(type: TestType, duration: integer): Represents a test that can be included in a requisition with its type and duration.
5. Lab(address: string, businessHours: string, registrationNumber: string, fees: decimal): Represents a lab where patients can book appointments for tests.
6. Appointment(lab: Lab, confirmationNumber: string, date: date, startTime: time, endTime: time, changeCancellationFee: decimal): Represents an appointment made by a patient at a lab for a test.
7. TestResult(test: Test, result: TestResult, report: string): Represents the result of a test including the test details, result, and accompanying report.

### Note:
- The classes and enumerations are structured based on the LabTracker software requirements provided in the description.
- Additional classes and attributes can be added as needed to further refine the class model.

#Description 
The LabTracker software helps (i) doctors manage the requisition of tests and examinations for patients and (ii) patients book appointments for tests and examinations at a lab. For the remainder of this description, tests and examinations are used interchangeably. 

For a requisition, a doctor must provide their numeric practitioner number and signature for verification as well as their full name, their address, and their phone number. The signature is a digital signature, i.e., an image of the actual signature of the doctor. Furthermore, the doctor indicates the date from which the requisition is valid. The requisition must also show the patient?? information including their alpha-numeric health number, first name and last name, date of birth, address, and phone number. A doctor cannot prescribe a test for themselves but can prescribe tests to someone else who is a doctor. 

Several tests can be combined on one requisition but only if they belong to the same group of tests. For example, only blood tests can be combined on one requisition or only ultrasound examinations can be combined. It is not possible to have a blood test and an ultrasound examination on the same requisition. For each test, its duration is defined by the lab network, so that it is possible to schedule appointments accordingly. The duration of a test is the same at each lab. For some kinds of tests, it does not matter how many tests are performed. They take as long as a single test. For example, several blood tests can be performed on a blood sample, i.e., it takes as long to draw the blood sample for a single blood test as it does for several blood tests. 

A doctor may also indicate that the tests on a requisition are to be repeated for a specified number of times and interval. The interval is either weekly, monthly, every half year, or yearly. All tests on a requisition are following the same repetition pattern. 

The doctor and the patient can view the results of each test (either negative or positive) as well as the accompanying report. 

A patient is required to make an appointment for some tests while others are walk-in only. For example, x-ray examinations require an appointment, but blood tests are walk-in only (i.e., it is not possible to make an appointment for a blood test). On the other hand, some tests only require a sample to be dropped off (e.g., a urine or stool sample). 

To make an appointment for a requisition, a patient selects the desired lab based on the lab?? address and business hours. For requisitions with repeated tests, a patient is only allowed to make one appointment at a time. The confirmation for an appointment also shows a confirmation number, the date as well as start/end times, and the name of the lab as well as its registration number. It is possible to change or cancel an appointment at any time but doing so within 24 hours of the appointment incurs a change/cancellation fee. Each lab determines its own fee and business hours. All labs are open every day of the year and offer all tests. The business hours of a lab do not change from one week to the next. Each day a lab is open from the day?? start time to its end time, i.e., there are no breaks.

Classes:

3. TestRequisition(doctor: Doctor, patient: Patient, tests: List<Test>, repetition: Repetition): Represents a test requisition with doctor, patient, tests, and repetition information.

7. Lab(address: String, businessHours: BusinessHours, registrationNumber: String, testsOffered: List<TestType>, fees: Map<TestType, Double>): Represents a lab where tests can be conducted with address, business hours, tests offered, and fees information.
